---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import { useTranslations } from '../../i18n';
const tr = useTranslations('en');
---
<Base title={tr.title_privacy} lang="en">

  <header class="corner">
    <div class="corner-left">
      <span class="dot"></span>
      <span>{tr.region}</span>
    </div>
    <div class="corner-right">
      <a href="/en/" class="back">{tr.back}</a>
      <nav class="lang-switcher">
        <a href={tr.alt_privacy}>{tr.lang_other}</a>
        <span class="lang-sep">·</span>
        <span class="lang-active">{tr.lang_self}</span>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main>
    <div class="content-page">
      <h1>{tr.privacy_title}</h1>
      <div class="subtitle">{tr.privacy_last_updated}</div>

      <p>
        Lacet is committed to protecting the privacy of people who visit
        <a href="https://lacet.ca">lacet.ca</a> and subscribe to our newsletter.
        This policy explains what information is collected, how it is used, and
        what your rights are.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Data controller</h2>
      <p>
        Lacet (Québec, Canada) is the controller of personal data collected through this site.
        For any question or request, contact us at
        <a href="mailto:info@lacet.ca">info@lacet.ca</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Information collected</h2>
      <p>When you subscribe to our newsletter, we collect:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your email address;</li>
        <li>The language chosen (French or English) at sign-up;</li>
        <li>The date and time of your consent.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        No other information is requested or collected about you without your explicit consent.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Purpose and legal basis</h2>
      <p>
        Your email address is used <strong>solely</strong> to send you the Lacet newsletter
        (announcements about the shop opening, new services, events). Processing is based on
        your <strong>explicit consent</strong>, given when you check the box at sign-up and
        confirm your email via the double opt-in link.
      </p>
      <p>
        Your contact details are never sold, rented, or shared for advertising purposes with
        third parties.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Processor</h2>
      <p>
        Newsletter delivery is operated by <strong>Brevo</strong> (formerly Sendinblue), a
        French company whose servers are located in the European Union. Brevo acts as a
        processor under Québec's Law 25 and the GDPR. Their policy is available at
        <a href="https://www.brevo.com/legal/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">brevo.com/legal/privacypolicy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Transfer outside Québec</h2>
      <p>
        Since Brevo is based in France, your data is transferred outside Québec. France is
        recognized as offering a level of protection equivalent to Québec under the GDPR.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Retention period</h2>
      <p>
        Your email address is kept as long as you remain subscribed to the newsletter. You
        can unsubscribe at any time via the link at the bottom of each email. Upon
        unsubscription, your address is removed from our mailing lists within 30 days.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Your rights</h2>
      <p>Under Québec's Law 25 and the GDPR, you have the following rights:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Access</strong>: know what data we hold about you;</li>
        <li><strong>Rectification</strong>: correct inaccurate information;</li>
        <li><strong>Erasure</strong>: request deletion of your data;</li>
        <li><strong>Withdrawal of consent</strong>: at any time, without justification;</li>
        <li><strong>Portability</strong>: receive your data in a readable format;</li>
        <li><strong>Complaint</strong>: with the Commission d'accès à l'information du Québec
          (<a href="https://www.cai.gouv.qc.ca" target="_blank" rel="noopener">cai.gouv.qc.ca</a>)
          or a competent European authority (CNIL in France).</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To exercise any of these rights, write to us at
        <a href="mailto:info@lacet.ca">info@lacet.ca</a>. We will respond within 30 days.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Cookies and tracking</h2>
      <p>
        This site uses <strong>no advertising tracking cookies</strong>, no third-party
        analytics tool (such as Google Analytics), and places no file on your device for
        marketing purposes. Only strictly necessary technical files (Cloudflare hosting)
        may be used.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Security</h2>
      <p>
        Communications between your browser and our servers are encrypted via HTTPS. Access
        keys to third-party services (such as Brevo) are stored encrypted and are never
        exposed publicly.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Changes</h2>
      <p>
        This policy may be updated to reflect changes in our practices or the law. The date
        of the last update is shown at the top of this page. In case of a material change,
        newsletter subscribers will be notified by email.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>

  <footer>
    <span>{tr.footer_copy}</span>
    <span class="footer-center"><a href={tr.nl_privacy_href}>{tr.footer_privacy}</a></span>
    <span>{tr.footer_domain}</span>
  </footer>

</Base>
